China Shouldn’t Alter Direction of Macroeconomic Controls, Adviser Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-23T08:58:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/china-shouldn-t-alter-direction-of-macroeconomic-controls-adviser-says.html
China  shouldn’t alter the direction
of its macroeconomic controls amid the current global turmoil,
Xia Bin, an academic adviser to the People’s Bank of China, said
in Beijing today.  The economy doesn’t face risks from an “overadjustment”
of policies, he said. China should stick to a prudent monetary
policy and should accelerate diversification of its foreign-
exchange reserves, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 navery2@bloomberg.net  